If you do not have the indilib development environment installed, see script build.sh
If it is already installed create within it a indi-3rdparty/indi-rolloffino directory
Copy the rolloffino files there.
create a build directory outside the the indi source tree and set default there.
Run cmake pointing to the source files
For example, copied from the build.sh file without the git clone:

$SRCDIR the directory containing the rolloffino files
$PROJDIR the directory immediately above the indilib indi tree directory

cp -p $SRCDIR/* $PROJDIR/indi/indi-3rdparty/indi-rolloffino
mkdir -p $PROJDIR/build/indi-3rdparty/indi-rolloffino
cd $PROJDIR/build/indi-3rdparty/indi-rolloffino
cmake -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr $PROJDIR/indi/indi-3rdparty/indi-rolloffino
sudo make install

